# Client (AngularJS) conventions

## Module layout

Features live in `client/app/<feature>/`:

- `<feature>.js` — module definition and ui-router states
- `<feature>.controller.js` — controller logic
- `<feature>.html` — template
- `<feature>.controller.spec.js` — unit tests (Karma)

Shared components: `client/components/<name>/` (directives, services).

Root module: `workspaceApp` in `client/app/app.js`.

## Patterns

- Use existing services (`client/components/auth/`, `metar.service.js`, etc.) before creating new ones
- ui-router states should match existing `$stateProvider` patterns in sibling modules
- Socket.io: use `btford.socket-io` as elsewhere in the app
- CSS colocated in feature or component folders

## Build

Client is assembled by Grunt (`Gruntfile.js`). New scripts must be wired through Grunt injector/dom-munger — do not assume ES modules or webpack.

## Do not

- Migrate to Angular 2+ or introduce React/Vue
- Change `$locationProvider.html5Mode` or default route without cause
- Modify `client/bower_components/` directly
